I am late. The future is already here🫣 and there’s no going back. I’ve been trying to slowly adopt and befriend AI. It was awkward at first, but wow I do see the enormous possibilities and it’s truly exciting!!

At the same time, the uncertain future change can be intimidating.🫥 At this point, I think the best thing I can do is to stay open-minded, learn about it, and see how we can live better together. So far, it seems we can get along.

How are you adapting to this new phase?

I want to share a famous quote by one of our all-time favorite artists, Henri Matisse. He arrived in the 19th century when photography was invented and started to spread, replacing portrait and landscape painters. It was a sensational era for many artists.

“I do not literally paint that table, but the emotion it produces upon me.”

-Henri Matisse

I know AI can generate incredible images in a second. But I still want to believe there is something only I can do. So we will learn how to collaborate and enhance each other. 
🤖😬🦾

Thank you, teacher Matisse. 💕🙏🏼

12 years ago, I adopted a cat when I didn’t even know if I could afford one. I thought I was rescuing her, but now, looking back, I realize that she was the one who rescued me. Whenever I had an emotional crisis and I couldn’t take care of myself, she was always there for me. She helped me find things I liked about myself, and that brought me many good things in my life. She turns 17 this week. I feel so privileged to have taken care of her all these years. She is my precious lucky black cat. 🐈‍⬛

By the way, did you know that November is #AdoptASeniorAnimalMonth? I hope many senior friends get a chance to find forever home. 

#adoptseniordogs #adoptseniorcats
